collections.name: "One Banana, Many Dreams"
collections.description:
"One Banana, Many Dreams"
This NFT, inspired by Maurizio Cattelan’s iconic Comedian, takes banana math and creativity to a whole new level. The original? One banana + one duct tape = $120,000. The buyer got no banana or tape but a certificate and DIY instructions.
So, why stop at one banana? Enter My Bunchonomics: the world’s first bunch of bananas NFT. Not one fruit, but FIVE bananas, each with duct tape. And the NFT?  It’s called "One Banana, Many Dreams." Revolutionary, right?
Now, the banana math:
•	1 banana + 1 tape = $100K (rounded).
•	5 bananas + 5 tapes = $500K.
My asking price? $500K, starting at just $1—because democracy matters.
Here’s the kicker: one taped banana sold for $6.2M in 2024. Following my Bunchonomics:
•	5 bananas x $6M = $30M.
Own a piece of history and math genius. Bid now and join the banana revolution! 🍌

collections.name: Light Capsule: Medicine or Addiction
collections.description:
The "Medicine or Addiction" collection is a provocative series of NFTs that transcends traditional art, highlighting the thin line between substances of comfort and those of obsession. Each piece in this collection features a unique light fixture crafted from upcycled wine bottles, meticulously transformed into capsule-shaped lamps.
The duality of the capsule shape symbolizes both addiction and medicine, urging viewers to reconsider societal labels and perceptions. This collection challenges the viewer to reflect on the transition from alcohol consumption to pharmaceutical usage, highlighting the often arbitrary distinction between legalized and criminalized substances.

collections.name: ZinnTrials
collections.description: The Zinn Trials collection is derived from two original works of art. All others are a variation of those distinct versions. They displaying obvious traits and are uniquely distinguishable. The work labeled "ZinnTrials 1 Aesthetic" is the creator's favorite. The one labeled "ZinnTrials 2 Basic" is based on an original. The work labeled "ZinnTrials 3 Classic" is also based on an original. All renditions are of the cover "A Glimpse of The Planet Zinn," a Science Fiction Fantasy Trilogy and exemplify the landscapes of the trial areas—ritualistic places where the youth of Zinn go and must complete a transition to achieve maturation. The two original illustrations were inspired after the author read the entire book to an artist who was retained to complete the artwork. The writer, Abron Toure, is the only African American who has authored 10 books, two trilogies, one a Science Fiction, the other on a Thought Experiments. All philosophical genres, distinctly strong slants towards science.
